						<summary>

						<p>On a boulder near the Mūḍagiri temple on the hill.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">16th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a grant of 10 <hi rend="italic">māna</hi> (of land) to Timapa by Nāgōjā, the <hi rend="italic">mokhāsi</hi> of Vaḍavaṭi in the presence of <hi rend="italic">nāḍagavuḍa</hi> and <hi rend="italic">samasta-praje</hi> (the people). There is a mention of maṭhada Saraya Mōchinayya.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in the cyclic year Yuva and the month Śrāvaṇa. It is in characters of about the 16th century. The cyclic year Yuva occurred twice during this century <hi rend="italic">viz.,</hi> Śaka 1437 (1515 A.D.) and Śaka 1497 (1575 A.D.).</p>						

						</summary>
